---
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - OurCouple" description="OurCouple Privacy Policy: Your data is encrypted. We can't read your messages, photos, or notes. No ads, no data selling, no third-party sharing." canonicalPath="/privacy">
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-1 pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Last updated: February 23, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Your Privacy Matters</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            OurCouple is built with privacy at its core. Your content is encrypted by default, which means <strong>only you and your partner can see it</strong>. Not even we can read your messages, photos, or notes.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            This policy applies to our website, waitlist, and mobile application.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">What We Collect</h2>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-text mb-3 mt-6">Account Information</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Display name</li>
            <li>Authentication data (via email, Google, or Apple Sign-In)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-text mb-3 mt-6">Your Content (Encrypted)</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">All content below is encrypted on your device before being stored on our servers:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Daily messages and photos of the day</li>
            <li>Shared moments and memories</li>
            <li>Shared notes</li>
            <li>Events and dates</li>
            <li>Daily question answers</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-text mb-3 mt-6">App Usage Data</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Virtual pet progress (name, level, experience)</li>
            <li>Couple streak data</li>
            <li>Push notification tokens</li>
            <li>App preferences and settings</li>
            <li>Crash reports and performance data (anonymized)</li>
            <li>Purchase and subscription status</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-text mb-3 mt-6">Analytics Data (Website & App)</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">We collect anonymous usage analytics to improve our product:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Page views and navigation patterns on our website</li>
            <li>Feature usage and interaction events in the app (e.g., which features are used most)</li>
            <li>Conversion funnels (signup, onboarding completion, subscription)</li>
            <li>Device type, browser, and operating system</li>
            <li>Referral source (how you found us)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
            This data is <strong>not linked to your encrypted content</strong> and cannot be used to read your messages, photos, or notes.
          </p>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-text mb-3 mt-6">Device Permissions</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Camera and photo library (to share photos with your partner)</li>
            <li>Notifications (to receive messages from your partner)</li>
            <li>Calendar (to sync couple events to your device calendar — Premium only)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-text mb-3 mt-6">Waitlist</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Email address only</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Encryption</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            All your personal content is automatically encrypted on your device before being sent to our servers. Only you and your partner have the keys to decrypt it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            This means:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Your messages, photos, and notes are encrypted by default</li>
            <li>Only encrypted data is stored on our servers</li>
            <li>Only you and your partner can decrypt your content</li>
            <li><strong>We cannot read your content</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            We use the following trusted services to operate the app. Each service only receives the minimum data necessary:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — Database hosting and authentication. Stores your encrypted content and account data.</li>
            <li><strong>RevenueCat</strong> — Subscription management. Receives your user ID and purchase information to manage premium access.</li>
            <li><strong>Sentry</strong> — Crash reporting. Receives anonymized error reports and performance data to help us fix bugs.</li>
            <li><strong>Expo</strong> — Push notification delivery. Receives your device push token to deliver notifications.</li>
            <li><strong>PostHog</strong> — Product analytics (website & app). Collects anonymous usage data (page views, feature usage, funnels) to help us improve the product. Data is hosted in the EU. Does not access your encrypted content.</li>
            <li><strong>DataFast</strong> — Lightweight website analytics. Collects anonymous page view data on our website only.</li>
            <li><strong>Apple / Google</strong> — Authentication (Sign in with Apple or Google). Receives only the data necessary to verify your identity.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4">
            None of these services can access your encrypted content.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Provide and maintain the app</li>
            <li>Sync your data between your devices</li>
            <li>Share your content with your connected partner</li>
            <li>Send push notifications (with your permission)</li>
            <li>Sync events to your device calendar (with your permission)</li>
            <li>Monitor app stability and fix crashes</li>
            <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve features and user experience</li>
            <li>Process premium subscriptions</li>
            <li>Notify you about product updates (waitlist)</li>
            <li>Respond to support requests</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">What We Don't Do</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>We don't read your content (we can't)</li>
            <li>We don't sell your data</li>
            <li>We don't show you ads</li>
            <li>We don't share your data with third parties for marketing</li>
            <li>We don't use your content for AI training or analytics</li>
            <li>We don't track your location</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Partner Sharing</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            OurCouple is designed for couples. When you connect with a partner, your shared content becomes visible to them:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Daily messages and photos of the day</li>
            <li>Shared moments, notes, and events</li>
            <li>Daily question answers</li>
            <li>Virtual pet progress</li>
            <li>Couple streak</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4">
            By inviting or accepting a partner, you consent to sharing this content with them. You can disconnect at any time in the app settings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Access and export your data</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Delete your account and all your data</li>
            <li>Unsubscribe from emails at any time</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4">
            Contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@vynse.dev" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">contact@vynse.dev</a> to exercise these rights. We'll respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li><strong>Active accounts:</strong> data is kept as long as your account is active</li>
            <li><strong>Deleted accounts:</strong> all data is permanently deleted within 30 days</li>
            <li><strong>Waitlist:</strong> email is kept until you unsubscribe or the app launches</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Age Requirement</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            OurCouple is for users 16 years and older. We do not knowingly collect data from anyone under 16.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            We may update this policy from time to time. We'll notify you of significant changes via email or in-app notification.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
            Questions about this Privacy Policy? Contact us:
          </p>
          <p class="text-primary font-medium">
            <a href="mailto:contact@vynse.dev">contact@vynse.dev</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-border">
        <a href="/" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark transition-colors font-medium">
          ← Back to Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
